        <h2>Volunteer Roles: Join Our Teams</h2>
        <p>We need volunteer prison oversight monitors to accompany our staff on facility inspections. This role requires a 6-month commitment, background clearance, and completion of our 16-hour training (provided free). Monitors visit facilities quarterly, document conditions, and write public reports. Currently, 12 volunteers support this work; we need 30 to cover all 13 state prisons.</p>
        <p>Our <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> program seeks peer outreach volunteers in Maricopa, Pima, and Coconino counties. You'll distribute naloxone and harm reduction supplies, connect people to treatment, and report policy barriers. This is boots-on-the-ground work requiring cultural humility and commitment to non-judgment. We provide training, supplies, and a $200 monthly stipend.</p>
