        <h2>Training Sign-Ups: Build Your Advocacy Skills</h2>
        <p>The <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training for Returning Citizens</strong> spring 2025 cohort runs March–May, meeting Wednesdays 6–8 PM at our Phoenix office with hybrid options. Topics include navigating the Arizona Legislature, testifying effectively, working with media, and campaign planning. Applications close February 20. Priority goes to directly impacted individuals; allies may apply for limited slots. The $500 stipend is distributed in two installments.</p>
        <p>Our <strong>ARTS in Prison & Think Motion</strong> program offers teaching artist training for formerly incarcerated creatives. This 8-week course prepares you to facilitate workshops inside ADCRR facilities. Graduates are eligible for paid teaching positions. Next session begins April 1. We cover all materials and provide mentorship from experienced arts staff.</p>
        <p>For organizations, we offer customized training on engaging directly impacted communities, trauma-informed advocacy, and the Seven Ps framework. We've trained staff at Phoenix Legal Action Network, Pima County Public Defender, and ACLU of Arizona. Request training via our contact form.</p>
